         full sweetness,        

445
00:15:43,142 --> 00:15:45,676
        but it also helps       
   break down the short ribs.   

446
00:15:45,678 --> 00:15:48,345
      We'll let it marinate     
         about 24 hours,        

447
00:15:48,347 --> 00:15:51,349
 and then it'll be ready to cook
    in the wood-fired grill.    

448
00:15:51,351 --> 00:15:54,752
  Then from there, we start off 
    with our handmade dough,    

449
00:15:54,754 --> 00:15:59,290
 shredded whole-milk mozzarella,
    thinly sliced scallions,    

450
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,625
   Korean barbecue short ribs.  

451
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,628
    And now it's ready to go.   

452
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:05,629
             FIERI:             
   Oh, but it's not done yet.   

453
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:07,898
  We finish it off with arugula 

454
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:11,169
   that's tossed in this spicy  
      gochujang vinaigrette     

455
00:16:11,171 --> 00:16:13,170
          and sprinkled         
       with sesame seeds.       

456
00:16:13,172 --> 00:16:15,773
                     ♪♪         

457
00:16:15,775 --> 00:16:17,642
    -Here's your Korean BBQ.    
           -Oh, yummy.          

458
00:16:17,644 --> 00:16:19,043
              MAN:              
  You got some greens in there, 

459
00:16:19,045 --> 00:16:20,978
then the meat is, like, velvet-y

460
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,114
        with a little bit       
