496
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:39,123
          so I figured          

497
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:41,525
    if I'm gonna step out of    
   my culinary comfort zone --  

498
00:17:41,527 --> 00:17:44,128
     ha! -- I'm dragging in     
       one of Minneapolis'      

499
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:47,565
  favorite culinary daredevils, 
         Andrew Zimmern.        

500
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:50,201
      And the Sunnyside is      
    one of his favorite pies.   

501
00:17:50,203 --> 00:17:51,736
        Pecorino Romano.        
     -It's Pecorino Romano.     

502
00:17:51,738 --> 00:17:52,870
         Then we go down        
        with some leeks.        

503
00:17:52,872 --> 00:17:54,872
     And what was the cream?    
          -Heavy cream.         

504
00:17:54,874 --> 00:17:56,406
   -Just regular heavy cream.   
              -Yep.             

505
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:57,741
   FIERI: Now we're going down  
          with some --          

506
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,543
               It's guanciale,  
                  actually.     

507
00:17:59,545 --> 00:18:01,345
         -Guanciale. Oh.        
